request.description:
In this case, some of the necessary parameters needed to issue the collection are taken from the invoice.

The following will be taken from the invoice:

*   Customer data;
*   The currency in which the invoice was issued - the currency of the collection will be the same as the currency of the invoice
*   The exchange rate used;
*   The language in which the invoice was issued - the language of the collection will be the same as the language of the invoice
*   The value of the collection is the invoice total


If these parameters are transmitted when using the method, they will be ignored since they will only be taken from the invoice.

It is not possible to partially collect an invoice.

The specific parameters are:

``` json
{
    "useInvoiceDetails": true,
    "invoicesList": {
        "seriesName": "{{invoiceSeriesName}}",
        "number": "0015"
    }
}

```

item.description:
## Possibilities of the SmartBill API:

*   Issuance of new invoices, deletion / cancellation of existing documents or restoration of canceled documents;
*   Access to invoices and estimates in PDF format;
*   Adding new products and customers to the database, by simply inserting an invoice or proforma;
*   Issuance and management of estimates, which can be converted into invoices after payment by the customer;
*   Efficient management of receipts by issuing receipts for an invoice;
*   Sending documents by e-mail to customers;
*   Access to stocks, series and VAT rates.
